researchResults.title: OpenAI reportedly finalizing $100B deal at more than $850B valuation
researchResults.description: OpenAI is reportedly getting close to closing a $100 billion deal, with backers including Amazon, Nvidia, SoftBank, and Microsoft. The deal would value the ChatGPT-maker at $850 billion.

researchResults.title: AI Impact Summit 2026
researchResults.description: A look at the partnerships and investments Google announced at the AI Impact Summit 2026.

researchResults.title: Why these startup CEOs don’t think AI will replace human roles
researchResults.description: The CEOs of Read AI and Lucidya told TechCrunch at Web Summit Qatar that they see AI tools replacing tasks, rather than workers.

researchResults.title: YouTube’s latest experiment brings its conversational AI tool to TVs
researchResults.description: YouTube is testing conversational AI on smart TVs, allowing viewers to ask the assistant questions related to the video they're watching on the big screen.

researchResults.title: Reddit is testing a new AI search feature for shopping
researchResults.description: A small group of users in the U.S. will start to see search results that include interactive product carousels with pricing, images, and direct where-to-buy links.

researchResults.title: Reload wants to give your AI agents a shared memory
researchResults.description: Reload announces a $2.275 million raise in a round led by Anthemis and the launch of its first AI employee, Epic.

researchResults.title: “No technology has me dreaming bigger than AI”
researchResults.description: CEO Sundar Pichai’s remarks at the opening ceremony of the AI Impact Summit 2026
